## Context
The corpus report reads as a pile of includes with section headings.
The data paper reads well because it has connective prose around each
table and figure. The corpus report needs the same treatment.

## Actions
1. Write introductory sentences before each table/figure explaining
   what the reader is about to see and why it matters
2. Write transitional paragraphs between sections
3. Ensure the Pipeline Overview flows into Corpus Construction
4. Ensure Corpus Contents section narrates the UMAP figures
   (what do they show? what should the reader notice?)
5. Fix CJK font rendering for bibCNRS query strings (xelatex
   needs a CJK-capable font fallback)

## Test
Corpus report reads as a coherent document, not a collage.

## Exit criteria
A reviewer can read the corpus report start to finish without
feeling they're jumping between disconnected fragments.
